snippet: The Obama administration said it would terminate health insurance for 115,000 people on Oct. 1 because they had failed to prove they were eligible for coverage.
abstract: Obama administration plans to terminate health insurance for 115,000 people on Oct 1, 2014, for failing to prove that they are United States citizens or legal immigrants eligible for coverage under the Affordable Care Act.
lead_paragraph: The Obama administration said it would terminate health insurance for 115,000 people on Oct. 1 because they had failed to prove they were eligible for coverage.
